The paper deals with evaluating the volume of balls in high-dimensional spaces, which is a problem in information theory and computational geometry. The use of determinants and asymptotic analysis suggests that the paper may belong to the cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.MG (Metric Geometry) sub-categories. The application of the results to rate-distortion analysis and source coding suggests that the paper may also belong to the cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) sub-categories. Finally, the use of moment-matching techniques suggests that the paper may belong to the cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) sub-category.
